1
00:01:27,587 --> 00:01:30,006
<i>♪ Do you believe in magic ♪</i>

2
00:01:30,381 --> 00:01:32,175
<i>♪ In a young girl's heart ♪</i>

3
00:01:32,258 --> 00:01:35,553
<i>♪ How the music can free her
Whenever it starts ♪</i>

4
00:01:35,720 --> 00:01:37,263
<i>♪ And it's magic... ♪</i>

5
00:01:37,722 --> 00:01:39,682
Why did you bring me to a college bar?

6
00:01:40,308 --> 00:01:41,392
I feel invisible here.

7
00:01:41,476 --> 00:01:44,187
Because it's about time
you get over that loser you were with.

8
00:01:44,312 --> 00:01:45,855
No guy is gonna wanna go

9
00:01:45,939 --> 00:01:48,024
with a single mom
who works as a secretary.

10
00:01:48,149 --> 00:01:50,777
Tonight, you are not a single mom,

11
00:01:50,860 --> 00:01:52,070
you are single.

12
00:01:52,153 --> 00:01:53,780
You're not a secretary,

13
00:01:54,155 --> 00:01:55,698
you have a secretary.

14
00:01:56,199 --> 00:01:57,033
And...

15
00:01:57,117 --> 00:01:58,368
how can you be invisible

16
00:01:58,451 --> 00:02:00,829
when that guy
has been staring at you all night?

17
00:02:11,089 --> 00:02:12,674
That's a beautiful ring.

18
00:02:16,469 --> 00:02:18,263
I didn't come to catch up, Ted.

19
00:02:21,724 --> 00:02:25,603
<i>♪ If you believe in magic
Come along with me ♪</i>

20
00:02:28,148 --> 00:02:29,607
This is my last quarter.

21
00:02:30,441 --> 00:02:31,568
Better make it a good one.

22
00:02:36,072 --> 00:02:37,824
I haven't seen you here before.

23
00:02:38,741 --> 00:02:41,035
It's my first time out
since I moved to Seattle.

24
00:02:41,661 --> 00:02:43,163
Do you remember the night we met?

25
00:02:44,789 --> 00:02:45,623
Yeah.

26
00:02:48,251 --> 00:02:50,670
I fell in love with you
the moment I saw you.

27
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:02,182
<i>♪ Now I don't hardly know her ♪</i>

28
00:03:04,642 --> 00:03:06,853
<i>♪ But I think I could love her ♪</i>

29
00:03:06,936 --> 00:03:09,022
What do you say we get out of here?

30
00:03:09,230 --> 00:03:10,690
Well, I don't even know your name.

31
00:03:23,161 --> 00:03:25,413
Thanks again for driving me home.

32
00:03:25,496 --> 00:03:26,956
Of course. It was really fun.

33
00:03:28,416 --> 00:03:29,417
This is...

34
00:03:30,043 --> 00:03:31,044
where I live.

35
00:03:31,169 --> 00:03:32,212
Okay.

36
00:03:37,217 --> 00:03:38,968
I guess I better get going.

37
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:43,890
Sorry, it's late

38
00:03:43,973 --> 00:03:45,391
and I have school tomorrow.

39
00:03:46,059 --> 00:03:47,727
Ted, this is Rachel, my, uh...

40
00:03:48,436 --> 00:03:49,270
my sitter.

41
00:03:50,438 --> 00:03:51,814
You can pay me later.

42
00:03:53,358 --> 00:03:54,275
Bye.

43
00:03:56,736 --> 00:03:58,571
I understand if you wanna go.

44
00:04:01,616 --> 00:04:03,243
Why would I wanna... do that?

45
00:04:10,166 --> 00:04:11,084
Come in.

46
00:04:25,348 --> 00:04:27,100
Are you sure you don't want to run?

47
00:04:55,169 --> 00:04:56,296
I'm really tired.

48
00:04:57,880 --> 00:04:59,173
Do you wanna rest?

49
00:05:02,969 --> 00:05:04,345
Come on. Let's rest.

50
00:05:41,174 --> 00:05:42,008
Hey.

51
00:05:43,259 --> 00:05:44,218
Hi.

52
00:05:44,344 --> 00:05:45,386
Coffee?

53
00:05:47,597 --> 00:05:48,431
Okay.

54
00:05:51,351 --> 00:05:52,185
Here you go.

55
00:05:56,689 --> 00:05:57,690
Good morning.

56
00:05:59,650 --> 00:06:01,194
You looked so pretty sleeping.

57
00:06:01,861 --> 00:06:03,988
Just... I didn't wanna wake you.

58
00:06:07,241 --> 00:06:08,076
Hey!

59
00:06:09,410 --> 00:06:11,079
Want to tell Mom about breakfast?

60
00:06:12,622 --> 00:06:14,916
I'm making omelettes.
I found some bacon...

61
00:06:16,042 --> 00:06:17,335
Do you like pancakes?

62
00:06:38,648 --> 00:06:41,567
<i>From January to July of 1974,</i>

63
00:06:41,651 --> 00:06:44,278
<i>the King County area was engulfed
in a wave of fear</i>

64
00:06:44,404 --> 00:06:46,531
<i>as young women were being
attacked and murdered</i>

65
00:06:46,614 --> 00:06:48,449
<i>with alarming regularity.</i>

66
00:06:48,533 --> 00:06:52,412
Georgann Hawkins was last seen
Monday evening shortly after midnight.

67
00:06:52,578 --> 00:06:54,455
She had been visiting at the Beta house

68
00:06:54,539 --> 00:06:58,835
and was returning to her house just a
half-block away down this alley.

69
00:06:59,919 --> 00:07:02,463
<i>King County police</i>
<i>have started their investigation</i>

70
00:07:02,547 --> 00:07:04,340
<i>after Janice Ott and Denise Naslund</i>

71
00:07:04,424 --> 00:07:06,426
<i>vanished from Lake Sammamish State Park.</i>

72
00:07:06,509 --> 00:07:08,678
<i>At least seven people at the crowded beach</i>

73
00:07:08,761 --> 00:07:11,180
<i>saw a smooth-talking man
with his arm in a cast</i>

74
00:07:11,264 --> 00:07:15,059
<i>asking several women to help him load
a boat onto a Volkswagen.</i>

75
00:07:15,726 --> 00:07:18,271
<i>A composite picture</i>
<i>was released to the news media.</i>

76
00:07:18,354 --> 00:07:19,856
<i>An intensive search</i>
<i>was mounted</i>

77
00:07:19,939 --> 00:07:21,732
<i>and police have been flooded
with phone calls</i>

78
00:07:21,816 --> 00:07:23,609
<i>from citizens who report
seeing the suspect.</i>

79
00:07:24,652 --> 00:07:26,195
<i>King County Sheriff's Department.</i>

80
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:27,488
<i>The guy in the paper, I...</i>

81
00:07:27,572 --> 00:07:29,365
<i>Take a breath.</i>
<i>Describe him for me, okay?</i>

82
00:07:29,490 --> 00:07:31,200
<i>What kind of car did he drive?</i>

83
00:07:36,497 --> 00:07:39,959
<i>♪ Looking like a fisherman ♪</i>

84
00:07:41,419 --> 00:07:44,005
<i>♪ Dropping a line in the sea ♪</i>

85
00:08:07,445 --> 00:08:10,573
Hi, officer. I think I must be lost

86
00:08:11,324 --> 00:08:12,950
You ran two stop signs, son.

87
00:08:13,034 --> 00:08:14,410
I know. I...

88
00:08:14,494 --> 00:08:15,661
couldn't make your car.

89
00:08:15,745 --> 00:08:17,747
The headlights were in my eyes
and, to be honest,

90
00:08:17,830 --> 00:08:19,790
I got a little bit spooked.

91
00:08:19,957 --> 00:08:21,876
- You got a license?
- Yes, absolutely.

92
00:08:23,169 --> 00:08:25,421
Somewhere... Yes. There..

93
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:31,761
So what's a kid from Seattle doing in
Granger, Utah this time of the morning?

94
00:08:31,969 --> 00:08:34,472
No, no. I live in Salt Lake now.

95
00:08:35,139 --> 00:08:36,349
I'm a law student

96
00:08:36,599 --> 00:08:38,518
over at, uh, the University of Utah.

97
00:08:38,808 --> 00:08:40,436
My girlfriend lives in Seattle.

98
00:08:41,562 --> 00:08:42,480
I'm actually...

99
00:08:43,147 --> 00:08:45,316
gonna propose to her
as soon as I graduate.

100
00:08:45,399 --> 00:08:46,526
Trying to save for that ring.

101
00:08:46,651 --> 00:08:49,320
So if you can find it in your heart
to let me off without a ticket,

102
00:08:49,403 --> 00:08:50,863
I would really appreciate it.

103
00:09:07,922 --> 00:09:08,965
Hello!

104
00:09:10,132 --> 00:09:10,967
Hello?

105
00:09:13,094 --> 00:09:14,095
Stay here.

106
00:09:17,890 --> 00:09:18,724
Hey.

107
00:09:20,268 --> 00:09:22,937
Oh! What the f... was that for?

108
00:09:23,020 --> 00:09:25,022
How many stop signs did you run?

109
00:09:35,324 --> 00:09:37,493
Have you ever been to the town of Murray?

110
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:39,036
What?

111
00:09:39,453 --> 00:09:41,539
You don't actually
believe this garbage, do you?

112
00:09:41,622 --> 00:09:43,291
It's in all the papers, Ted!

113
00:09:43,374 --> 00:09:45,001
Number six, step forward.

114
00:09:45,334 --> 00:09:47,503
If you don't stop screaming,
I'm gonna kill you.

115
00:09:48,212 --> 00:09:50,256
Number seven, step forward.

116
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:54,760
If you don't stop screaming,
I'm gonna kill you.

117
00:09:56,429 --> 00:09:59,348
Now, miss. Do you recognize
any of these suspects?

118
00:10:02,518 --> 00:10:03,603
Number seven.

119
00:10:04,186 --> 00:10:05,187
<i>Please rise.</i>

120
00:10:06,147 --> 00:10:08,733
You are hereby charged
with aggravated kidnapping

121
00:10:08,816 --> 00:10:10,484
and attempted criminal assault.

122
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,446
I got your bail reduced.

123
00:10:13,529 --> 00:10:15,323
You'll be in Seattle with Liz tomorrow.

124
00:10:17,241 --> 00:10:20,202
I didn't tell you 'cause
I didn't want you to freak out.

125
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:21,996
Come here.

126
00:10:28,502 --> 00:10:30,046
I know it's hard being apart,

127
00:10:30,338 --> 00:10:32,506
but we only have
four semesters between us...

128
00:10:33,049 --> 00:10:35,801
and our place in the Sound
with a dog and a car.

129
00:10:38,387 --> 00:10:40,097
Just like we always dreamed.

130
00:10:40,181 --> 00:10:43,142
- Ted!
- Oh, monkey! Hey, what's up?

131
00:10:43,225 --> 00:10:44,769
Good to see you!

132
00:10:45,311 --> 00:10:49,398
Oh, man! This sack of potatoes
is getting pretty dang heavy!

133
00:10:49,523 --> 00:10:51,817
Oh, hey!

134
00:10:51,901 --> 00:10:53,069
I'm getting dizzy.

135
00:10:53,235 --> 00:10:54,779
Oh, come here! Gimme a hug.

136
00:10:54,945 --> 00:10:57,239
Good to see you. I missed you. Mmm.

137
00:11:01,744 --> 00:11:03,579
Can we get ice cream later?

138
00:11:03,663 --> 00:11:05,373
That is such a good idea!

139
00:11:05,456 --> 00:11:07,541
I wish I could but I can't.

140
00:11:07,708 --> 00:11:08,542
I'm sorry.

141
00:11:08,626 --> 00:11:10,795
I have to pull an all-nighter tonight
at the law library.

142
00:11:11,337 --> 00:11:12,296
All-nighter?

143
00:11:12,546 --> 00:11:15,508
Yeah, I gotta make sure I'm the most
prepared attorney in the courtroom

144
00:11:15,591 --> 00:11:16,676
once my trial starts.

145
00:11:18,219 --> 00:11:20,179
Why did she pick you out of the lineup?

146
00:11:21,889 --> 00:11:25,351
My lawyer found out that the police
showed her my picture beforehand.

147
00:11:26,686 --> 00:11:27,603
Twice.

148
00:11:28,604 --> 00:11:29,897
<i>Of course I looked familiar.</i>

149
00:11:32,024 --> 00:11:33,567
That's not even the worst part, Liz.

150
00:11:35,361 --> 00:11:36,570
What happened in Utah

151
00:11:36,904 --> 00:11:38,489
wasn't just dumb luck.

152
00:11:40,616 --> 00:11:42,368
The police already had my name.

153
00:11:43,202 --> 00:11:44,745
Someone gave it to them.

154
00:11:48,207 --> 00:11:51,168
Someone gave your name
to the authorities in Utah?

155
00:11:51,252 --> 00:11:52,086
Mm-hmm.

156
00:11:52,586 --> 00:11:54,505
Do you have any idea
who'd do that to you?

157
00:11:58,050 --> 00:11:59,885
Look, do you see that car out there?

158
00:12:02,012 --> 00:12:04,098
It's been following me since I got back.

159
00:12:04,765 --> 00:12:07,143
Either I'm going crazy

160
00:12:07,601 --> 00:12:08,769
or I'm being set up.

161
00:12:12,273 --> 00:12:13,107
Done!

162
00:12:13,274 --> 00:12:14,316
It's a thresher shark.

163
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:16,610
They have a tail
as long as their whole body.

164
00:12:16,861 --> 00:12:19,447
A tail as long as their whole body?
That's crazy!

165
00:12:20,156 --> 00:12:21,574
How the heck did you get
so smart?

166
00:12:21,657 --> 00:12:23,200
I get it from my mom.

167
00:12:23,659 --> 00:12:25,077
You do, don't you?

168
00:12:27,037 --> 00:12:27,872
Aw.

169
00:12:31,792 --> 00:12:33,377
Everything is gonna be okay.

170
00:14:01,257 --> 00:14:02,466
Uh, excuse me, sir.

171
00:14:02,550 --> 00:14:04,176
Could you come with me, please?

172
00:14:05,344 --> 00:14:06,512
Is there something wrong?

173
00:14:06,595 --> 00:14:08,806
Just come with me, please.
Bring your coat.

174
00:14:10,349 --> 00:14:11,308
Okay.

175
00:14:18,357 --> 00:14:20,401
You know this is ridiculous, right?

176
00:14:20,484 --> 00:14:21,569
We're closing soon anyway.

177
00:14:21,694 --> 00:14:23,279
So, it's just better for everybody.

178
00:14:23,362 --> 00:14:24,989
Oh, really? You're closing?

179
00:14:26,031 --> 00:14:27,366
You close in 45 minutes.

180
00:14:33,330 --> 00:14:34,248
Hey!

181
00:14:35,165 --> 00:14:36,166
Hey, hey!

182
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:37,668
Who are you?

183
00:14:37,751 --> 00:14:38,836
Hey, stop! Hey!

184
00:14:38,919 --> 00:14:40,296
I know you're following me!

185
00:14:40,421 --> 00:14:42,214
What are you... Who sent you?

186
00:14:56,645 --> 00:14:57,730
What are you doing?

187
00:14:57,897 --> 00:14:59,899
Reading. I'm prepping for the trial.

188
00:14:59,982 --> 00:15:03,027
- With a flashlight under the sheets?
- Yeah, I didn't wanna wake you up.

189
00:15:08,157 --> 00:15:09,158
You okay?

190
00:15:10,284 --> 00:15:11,160
Uh...

191
00:15:11,994 --> 00:15:13,203
I think we should get married.

192
00:15:25,549 --> 00:15:27,676
Why is this happening right now?

193
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:30,262
A couple of college girls
disappeared last year

194
00:15:30,346 --> 00:15:32,264
around the University of Washington.

195
00:15:32,348 --> 00:15:33,807
And two more girls

196
00:15:33,891 --> 00:15:38,187
vanished in broad daylight
in a crowded state park in, uh...

197
00:15:38,854 --> 00:15:40,481
near Seattle. You remember that?

198
00:15:41,106 --> 00:15:42,566
- Lake... Lake Sammamish?
- Yeah.

199
00:15:42,942 --> 00:15:45,861
Witnesses say
some guy was asking girls to, uh...

200
00:15:46,070 --> 00:15:49,114
help him put a sailboat on top of a car,
and police put out a sketch.

201
00:15:49,239 --> 00:15:51,575
I had the same car as the suspect,
a VW Bug...

202
00:15:51,659 --> 00:15:54,620
and my friends teased me about
the resemblance to the sketch.

203
00:15:55,162 --> 00:15:57,039
But, geez, nobody was serious.

204
00:15:57,122 --> 00:15:58,290
Someone must have been.

205
00:15:58,457 --> 00:16:01,835
Because your name landed
on a suspect list in Seattle.

206
00:16:02,753 --> 00:16:04,880
When Utah police got wind of that...

207
00:16:04,964 --> 00:16:07,007
they started looking at you
with a lot more interest,

208
00:16:07,091 --> 00:16:09,843
because something similar
is happening to the girls right here.

209
00:16:10,928 --> 00:16:13,055
I was kicking him and screaming.

210
00:16:13,681 --> 00:16:16,558
He held a small black gun
to my head and said,

211
00:16:17,518 --> 00:16:19,228
"If you don't stop screaming

212
00:16:19,353 --> 00:16:20,688
I'm going to kill you.

213
00:16:20,854 --> 00:16:22,481
I'll blow your brains out."

214
00:16:22,648 --> 00:16:26,068
Then I fell backwards out of his car
and ran as fast as I could.

215
00:16:26,485 --> 00:16:28,487
As best you recall, Carol...

216
00:16:29,154 --> 00:16:31,991
is the man who approached you
present in court today?

217
00:16:33,659 --> 00:16:34,743
Mm-hmm.

218
00:16:34,994 --> 00:16:35,828
Yes.

219
00:16:36,453 --> 00:16:38,330
Can you point where he's seated?

220
00:16:45,546 --> 00:16:48,841
Let the record state the identification
of the defendant.

221
00:16:54,346 --> 00:16:56,056
No more questions, Your Honor.

222
00:16:56,557 --> 00:16:57,725
Hi, Miss Daronch.

223
00:16:58,392 --> 00:17:00,602
Had the police shown you
a picture of my client

224
00:17:00,686 --> 00:17:04,064
prior to your identification of him
at the October 2nd lineup?

225
00:17:05,107 --> 00:17:05,941
Yes.

226
00:17:06,358 --> 00:17:08,234
You did in fact
pick his picture out of a pile

227
00:17:08,318 --> 00:17:09,987
but when asked specifically

228
00:17:10,194 --> 00:17:13,281
why you chose his picture, you stated

229
00:17:13,781 --> 00:17:17,953
"It looks something like him,
but I really couldn't say for sure."

230
00:17:18,537 --> 00:17:19,621
Is that correct?

231
00:17:21,373 --> 00:17:22,332
Mm-hmm.

232
00:17:22,833 --> 00:17:27,046
The only remotely corroborative evidence
you provided was a make of a vehicle.

233
00:17:27,128 --> 00:17:30,382
It's a Volkswagen, one of the most popular
cars in America.

234
00:17:30,591 --> 00:17:34,136
Yet his Volkswagen looks
nothing like your description.

235
00:17:34,219 --> 00:17:35,429
How do you square that?

236
00:17:36,430 --> 00:17:38,891
They told me it was supposed to be...

237
00:17:38,974 --> 00:17:40,809
Hmm. I'm sorry, I couldn't hear you.

238
00:17:42,978 --> 00:17:45,064
They told me it was supposed
to be the car.

239
00:17:45,856 --> 00:17:46,815
Who did?

240
00:17:47,316 --> 00:17:48,650
Who told you that, Miss Daronch?

241
00:17:54,823 --> 00:17:56,909
We all sympathize with your pain.

242
00:17:56,992 --> 00:17:59,078
It is horrible what you went through.

243
00:17:59,161 --> 00:18:00,829
But the fact of the matter is

244
00:18:01,246 --> 00:18:02,581
you identified my client

245
00:18:02,664 --> 00:18:04,958
because law enforcement
wanted you to, didn't you?

246
00:18:06,418 --> 00:18:07,294
I...

247
00:18:08,962 --> 00:18:11,048
No. No further questions, Your Honor.

248
00:18:18,931 --> 00:18:21,100
I know the trial
seems to be going well,

249
00:18:21,183 --> 00:18:23,102
but you sure
you want to do this right now?

250
00:18:23,227 --> 00:18:24,853
Just because we don't have the house yet,

251
00:18:24,937 --> 00:18:26,688
doesn't mean we can't look for the dog.

252
00:18:26,814 --> 00:18:28,190
- Right?
- Mm-hmm. Okay.

253
00:18:30,234 --> 00:18:31,110
Carole Ann?

254
00:18:31,193 --> 00:18:32,027
Ah!

255
00:18:32,444 --> 00:18:35,280
- Hi, stranger.
- Oh, my God. Hi. Wow.

256
00:18:37,199 --> 00:18:38,992
What are you... What are you doing here?

257
00:18:39,284 --> 00:18:40,327
Do you live in Utah now?

258
00:18:40,494 --> 00:18:44,081
No. I'm just visiting
some friends that work here.

259
00:18:44,748 --> 00:18:46,375
- Great.
