It is a capital murder case.

1239
01:14:47,149 --> 01:14:53,864
The court has already ruled
on this witness' expertise, counselor.

1240
01:14:54,072 --> 01:14:56,575
And you are skating on thin ice.

1241
01:14:56,658 --> 01:14:59,870
And ice does not last long in Florida.

1242
01:15:00,537 --> 01:15:01,413
Yes, Your Honor.

1243
01:15:09,379 --> 01:15:11,590
<i>The case of Ted Bundy,</i>
<i>a man suspected of murdering</i>

1244
01:15:11,673 --> 01:15:13,175
<i>two Florida State coeds</i>

1245
01:15:13,258 --> 01:15:15,302
<i>and beating three others
a year and a half ago...</i>

1246
01:15:18,472 --> 01:15:19,723
Would you mind getting that?

1247
01:15:20,682 --> 01:15:21,808
Uh, yeah, sure.

1248
01:15:24,603 --> 01:15:25,562
Hello?

1249
01:15:26,104 --> 01:15:27,147
Who is this?

1250
01:15:29,149 --> 01:15:30,234
Is this Ted?

1251
01:15:31,735 --> 01:15:33,362
Yes, this is Ted.

1252
01:15:33,862 --> 01:15:35,405
<i>And I would like to speak to Liz.</i>

1253
01:15:36,156 --> 01:15:37,741
You can't call her anymore.

1254
01:15:38,367 --> 01:15:39,409
You're killing her.

1255
01:15:40,494 --> 01:15:42,955
Then, will you please
give her a message for me?

1256
01:15:43,539 --> 01:15:45,123
Can you do that, please?

1257
01:15:46,208 --> 01:15:47,626
<i>Can you tell her, um..</i>

1258
01:15:50,546 --> 01:15:52,172
Can you tell her that I love her?

1259
01:16:58,322 --> 01:16:59,281
Oh, fuck.

1260
01:17:09,625 --> 01:17:10,709
Oh, wow!

1261
01:17:15,631 --> 01:17:16,548
Ted?

1262
01:17:19,801 --> 01:17:20,761
Ted?

1263
01:17:23,013 --> 01:17:23,972
Look at me!

1264
01:17:24,973 --> 01:17:25,849
Huh?

1265
01:17:26,308 --> 01:17:27,392
Do you...

1266
01:17:28,727 --> 01:17:29,853
Do you still love her?

1267
01:17:31,521 --> 01:17:33,148
What are you talking about? Who?

1268
01:17:33,815 --> 01:17:34,733
Oh, my God.

1269
01:17:35,150 --> 01:17:36,943
- No...
- Oh, my God. I'm so stupid.

1270
01:17:37,027 --> 01:17:37,986
Carole Ann, just...

1271
01:17:38,070 --> 01:17:41,156
I mean, I just uprooted
my entire life for you!

1272
01:17:41,323 --> 01:17:42,532
She's not here!

1273
01:17:43,492 --> 01:17:45,494
- But you love her!
- I don't! I don't!

1274
01:17:45,577 --> 01:17:46,828
She abandoned me!

1275
01:17:46,912 --> 01:17:48,163
She left me.

1276
01:17:48,664 --> 01:17:49,790
She's gone.

1277
01:17:50,874 --> 01:17:52,376
What about me?

1278
01:17:53,669 --> 01:17:54,670
I love you.

1279
01:17:54,836 --> 01:17:55,754
You're here.

1280
01:17:56,630 --> 01:17:58,090
You're right here.

1281
01:17:58,173 --> 01:18:00,092
I almost married that girl.

1282
01:18:04,012 --> 01:18:05,639
And... and you know what?

1283
01:18:06,056 --> 01:18:08,100
You're the one I should've married.

1284
01:18:10,185 --> 01:18:11,478
Do you mean that?

1285
01:18:12,562 --> 01:18:13,522
Yeah.

1286
01:18:14,356 --> 01:18:15,565
Just imagine it.

1287
01:18:18,485 --> 01:18:19,569
I'll get out of here.

1288
01:18:21,238 --> 01:18:22,364
We can get a house...

1289
01:18:23,573 --> 01:18:24,616
on the Sound.

1290
01:18:26,284 --> 01:18:27,411
With a Mercedes...

1291
01:18:29,204 --> 01:18:30,372
and a dog.

1292
01:18:32,124 --> 01:18:33,583
I can hear him barking.

1293
01:18:35,252 --> 01:18:36,128
Can you?

1294
01:18:38,422 --> 01:18:39,840
I'm allergic to dogs.

1295
01:18:42,300 --> 01:18:43,760
But that sounds nice.

1296
01:18:44,803 --> 01:18:45,971
Oh, Ted.

1297
01:18:48,432 --> 01:18:50,308
I just wish we didn't have to wait.

1298
01:18:52,185 --> 01:18:53,770
Who says we have to wait?

1299
01:18:54,688 --> 01:18:55,731
We don't.

1300
01:19:00,485 --> 01:19:01,737
Miss Boone.

1301
01:19:02,529 --> 01:19:07,534
Did you visit me while I was being held
in Florida in custody in February, 1978?

1302
01:19:08,452 --> 01:19:10,203
Yes. Yes, I did.

1303
01:19:10,287 --> 01:19:11,872
And to the best of your memory,

1304
01:19:11,955 --> 01:19:14,875
did I have any sort of chip
in my front tooth at that time?

1305
01:19:14,958 --> 01:19:17,294
No. No, you most definitely did not.

1306
01:19:17,377 --> 01:19:18,295
Your Honor...

1307
01:19:19,254 --> 01:19:21,298
I think you see what I'm getting at here.

1308
01:19:22,174 --> 01:19:25,886
I would like to subpoena all newspapers
to turn over their negatives of me.

1309
01:19:26,636 --> 01:19:31,016
If the chip did not occur
until March, 1978,

1310
01:19:31,099 --> 01:19:33,518
two months after the Chi Omega crimes

1311
01:19:33,602 --> 01:19:35,771
and the state's odontologists
say otherwise,

1312
01:19:35,937 --> 01:19:39,357
the state's odontologists have obviously
taken my teeth

1313
01:19:39,441 --> 01:19:42,194
and twisted them
every which way but loose

1314
01:19:42,277 --> 01:19:43,278
to fit.

1315
01:19:44,237 --> 01:19:48,283
Son, you can jump up and down
and hang from the chandelier,

1316
01:19:48,366 --> 01:19:52,537
but the court will not dash out
for new evidence at your command.

1317
01:19:54,831 --> 01:19:57,375
Is there no work ethic
left here in Florida?

1318
01:19:57,459 --> 01:19:58,960
You impress me not, sir.

1319
01:19:59,044 --> 01:20:00,670
The feeling is mutual, Your Honor.

1320
01:20:00,754 --> 01:20:02,589
I'm sure it is. Bless your heart.

1321
01:20:02,672 --> 01:20:04,758
And unless there is anything else,

1322
01:20:04,841 --> 01:20:06,468
Miss Boone may be excused.

1323
01:20:06,593 --> 01:20:09,179
No, there is one... Just one more thing.

1324
01:20:09,763 --> 01:20:10,722
Your Honor...

1325
01:20:17,187 --> 01:20:18,355
Will you marry me?

1326
01:20:21,441 --> 01:20:22,275
Your Honor...

1327
01:20:22,526 --> 01:20:24,319
Yes.

1328
01:20:27,572 --> 01:20:29,032
Then I do hereby...

1329
01:20:29,908 --> 01:20:30,826
marry you.

1330
01:20:30,909 --> 01:20:32,494
Are you shitting me? Objection!

1331
01:20:32,577 --> 01:20:33,495
Your Honor...

1332
01:20:33,578 --> 01:20:35,747
a public declaration properly phrased,

1333
01:20:35,831 --> 01:20:37,958
in an open courtroom,
in the presence of court officers

1334
01:20:38,041 --> 01:20:40,377
constitutes a lawful marriage
here in Florida.

1335
01:20:41,503 --> 01:20:42,754
Indeed it does.

1336
01:20:49,594 --> 01:20:53,139
<i>Prosecutors dismissed</i>
<i>Bundy's marriage proposal as a charade...</i>

1337
01:20:55,851 --> 01:20:57,602
Was it him who called the other day?

1338
01:21:01,147 --> 01:21:03,608
I know you unplug the phones
when I fall asleep.

1339
01:21:04,943 --> 01:21:06,111
What did he say?

1340
01:21:06,903 --> 01:21:08,822
- It doesn't matter.
- What did he say?

1341
01:21:10,407 --> 01:21:11,491
He froze.

1342
01:21:11,616 --> 01:21:14,703
He froze because he knew
that I knew what he was.

1343
01:21:14,786 --> 01:21:17,289
They're going to send him
to the chair, Liz.

1344
01:21:17,372 --> 01:21:19,332
And that seems
like an easier out than this torture

1345
01:21:19,416 --> 01:21:22,085
you're putting yourself through
because you won't let him go.

1346
01:21:22,168 --> 01:21:24,337
He's killing you
because you're letting him.

1347
01:21:25,422 --> 01:21:28,842
You're just jealous because Ted and I
have a bond you and I never could.

1348
01:21:30,427 --> 01:21:32,012
You're just trying to hurt me.

1349
01:21:32,929 --> 01:21:33,972
Get out.

1350
01:21:36,766 --> 01:21:37,893
Get out!

1351
01:21:38,059 --> 01:21:39,728
- You need to let him go.
- Get out!

1352
01:21:39,811 --> 01:21:43,899
- You need... Let him go!
- Get out! Get out! Get out!

1353
01:21:44,024 --> 01:21:45,859
Shh.

1354
01:21:45,942 --> 01:21:46,902
It's okay.

1355
01:21:47,277 --> 01:21:49,154
I wish I could take it all back.

1356
01:21:49,237 --> 01:21:50,405
It's okay.

1357
01:21:54,034 --> 01:21:55,076
Take what back?

1358
01:21:55,368 --> 01:21:59,205
Why do you act like you're responsible
for the things that happened to him?

1359
01:22:07,172 --> 01:22:09,382
I'm the one
who gave his name to the police.

1360
01:22:10,800 --> 01:22:13,720
<i>He was described</i>
<i>as 5'7 to 5'8...</i>

1361
01:22:13,803 --> 01:22:17,265
<i>neck-length hair,
brown to light brown, dark tan,</i>

1362
01:22:17,390 --> 01:22:20,143
<i>160 pounds, cast on the left arm.</i>

1363
01:22:20,226 --> 01:22:21,978
<i>King County Sheriff's Department.</i>

1364
01:22:22,062 --> 01:22:24,522
Back when those girls disappeared
from Lake Sammamish

1365
01:22:24,981 --> 01:22:27,317
I saw the sketch.

1366
01:22:27,400 --> 01:22:30,445
It's a minor resemblance,
but it's very, very minor and...

1367
01:22:30,528 --> 01:22:32,072
<i>What kind of car does he drive?</i>

1368
01:22:32,155 --> 01:22:34,032
It's a 1968 Volkswagen Bug.

1369
01:22:34,240 --> 01:22:35,742
But it's kind of a light beige...

1370
01:22:35,825 --> 01:22:37,118
<i>Let me stop you right there.</i>

1371
01:22:37,202 --> 01:22:39,454
<i>It's the right car,
but it's the wrong color.</i>

1372
01:22:40,163 --> 01:22:41,247
<i>He's not the guy.</i>

1373
01:22:41,414 --> 01:22:44,000
<i>I can put his name down
if it'll help you sleep at night.</i>

1374
01:22:44,292 --> 01:22:46,294
<i>- What is his name?</i>
- Um...

1375
01:22:48,421 --> 01:22:49,339
Ted.

1376
01:22:50,840 --> 01:22:52,008
Ted Bundy.

1377
01:22:52,092 --> 01:22:53,677
I could be the reason that he's there.

1378
01:22:53,760 --> 01:22:55,261
Because everyone's assuming

1379
01:22:55,345 --> 01:22:57,597
that all these other murders
were done by Ted

1380
01:22:57,722 --> 01:23:00,141
and all I did
was call his name in to Seattle,

1381
01:23:00,225 --> 01:23:03,311
because of a sketch
that looked kind of like him.

1382
01:23:03,728 --> 01:23:05,063
You were the one that told them.

1383
01:23:06,022 --> 01:23:07,649
You shouldn't be ashamed of that.

1384
01:23:08,066 --> 01:23:09,442
If you told them that...

1385
01:23:09,776 --> 01:23:11,486
He... he deserves it, Liz.

1386
01:23:11,653 --> 01:23:13,196
Liz, you did the right thing.

1387
01:23:16,533 --> 01:23:18,368
You just gotta let him go.

1388
01:23:20,370 --> 01:23:23,289
Mr. Simpson, your closing argument.

1389
01:23:31,256 --> 01:23:32,924
Ladies and gentlemen of the jury,

1390
01:23:34,050 --> 01:23:37,804
you have been witness
to the unspeakable horrors

1391
01:23:38,471 --> 01:23:40,390
of the defendant's heinous crimes.

1392
01:23:41,349 --> 01:23:42,517
You've seen...

1393
01:23:42,851 --> 01:23:43,893
ghastly injuries,

1394
01:23:44,352 --> 01:23:46,896
smashed in faces, broken jaws...

1395
01:23:51,109 --> 01:23:53,403
The bite-mark carnage of a predator.

1396
01:23:54,487 --> 01:23:55,697
Ladies and gentlemen...

1397
01:23:56,322 --> 01:23:57,824
there are two ways

1398
01:23:58,533 --> 01:24:00,452
for police to investigate crimes.

1399
01:24:01,494 --> 01:24:03,079
They can go to a crime scene...

1400
01:24:04,414 --> 01:24:05,707
<i>search for clues</i>

1401
01:24:06,124 --> 01:24:09,669
<i>and follow those clues
to a logical conclusion...</i>

1402
01:24:09,753 --> 01:24:12,338
We have provided forensic expert testimony

1403
01:24:12,422 --> 01:24:14,966
<i>to corroborate every last bit of evidence.</i>

1404
01:24:15,091 --> 01:24:17,635
...or they can begin with a suspect,

1405
01:24:18,887 --> 01:24:21,014
decide on that suspect,

1406
01:24:21,097 --> 01:24:24,100
and then somehow
make all of the evidence fit

1407
01:24:24,184 --> 01:24:26,311
only that suspect.

1408
01:24:26,394 --> 01:24:28,897
You've seen
the bottle of hair mist he used

1409
01:24:28,980 --> 01:24:30,899
to sexually penetrate
one of the victims,

1410
01:24:30,982 --> 01:24:34,486
in a manner so savage
it ruptured her internal organs.

1411
01:24:34,819 --> 01:24:38,907
It is clearly a charade
to cast an innocent man

1412
01:24:38,990 --> 01:24:42,327
as some sort of monster in a horror film.

1413
01:24:42,410 --> 01:24:44,579
We have placed the defendant
at the scene of the crime...

1414
01:24:44,662 --> 01:24:46,289
Their own witness testified

1415
01:24:46,372 --> 01:24:49,417
that the man wore a mask,
obscuring half of his face.

1416
01:24:49,501 --> 01:24:53,296
You've seen the oak log he used
to bludgeon these poor victims.

1417
01:24:53,588 --> 01:24:54,839
The lighting was low.

1418
01:24:54,923 --> 01:24:58,426
The State of Florida has proved beyond
all reasonable doubt

1419
01:24:58,843 --> 01:25:01,262
that the defendant
Theodore Robert Bundy

1420
01:25:01,346 --> 01:25:04,682
is guilty of two murders
in the first-degree

1421
01:25:04,766 --> 01:25:06,643
and three attempted murders.

1422
01:25:06,726 --> 01:25:08,853
Ladies and gentlemen, I am...

1423
01:25:10,021 --> 01:25:11,731
that innocent suspect.

1424
01:25:14,901 --> 01:25:18,113
Ted, Ted, is this really just a case
of wrong place, wrong time?

1425
01:25:18,404 --> 01:25:20,532
You know, police,
they just wanna solve crimes.

1426
01:25:20,615 --> 01:25:22,826
And sometimes they don't think things
all the way through.

1427
01:25:22,909 --> 01:25:25,620
They are willing to take
the convenient alternative.

1428
01:25:25,703 --> 01:25:28,206
And in this case,
the convenient alternative was me.

1429
01:25:28,289 --> 01:25:29,874
Ted, we have a verdict.

1430
01:25:30,500 --> 01:25:31,709
They've come to verdict.

1431
01:25:31,876 --> 01:25:34,003
Oh, my gosh. Seven hours.

1432
01:25:34,879 --> 01:25:35,880
Well...

1433
01:25:36,840 --> 01:25:37,799
bless their hearts.

1434
01:25:38,925 --> 01:25:40,218
Ted.

1435
01:25:41,719 --> 01:25:43,805
You know that future you saw for us?

1436
01:25:44,347 --> 01:25:46,266
The one with the house
and the dog and the car?

1437
01:25:47,308 --> 01:25:48,977
Well, yeah. Yeah.

1438
01:25:49,602 --> 01:25:50,478
Well...

1439
01:25:51,271 --> 01:25:53,606
now there's going to be another part
to that future.

1440
01:25:56,985 --> 01:25:57,861
Ted...

1441
01:25:58,027 --> 01:25:59,154
it's time to go.

1442
01:26:00,613 --> 01:26:01,489
Ted.

1443
01:26:01,906 --> 01:26:03,700
Yeah... yeah, I...

1444
01:26:03,783 --> 01:26:05,660
I'll... One... just one moment. Um...

1445
01:26:13,960 --> 01:26:15,295
Let's go finish this thing.

1446
01:26:23,011 --> 01:26:27,140
I am in receipt
of the jury's verdict, Bailiff.

1447
01:26:27,932 --> 01:26:32,187
Would you deliver this to the clerk
for pronouncement?

1448
01:26:34,647 --> 01:26:36,524
Will the defendant rise?

1449
01:26:42,030 --> 01:26:44,657
<i>We, the jury,
in Miami-Dade County, Florida,</i>

1450
01:26:44,741 --> 01:26:47,827
find the defendant Theodore Robert Bundy,

1451
01:26:48,119 --> 01:26:51,456
on the count of murder
in the first degree of Lisa Levy,

1452
01:26:52,040 --> 01:26:53,291
<i>guilty as charged.</i>

1453
01:26:53,458 --> 01:26:56,502
On the count of murder in the first degree
of Margaret Bowman,

1454
01:26:56,586 --> 01:26:57,712
guilty as charged.

1455
01:26:57,795 --> 01:27:01,549
On the count of attempted murder
in the first degree of Karen Chandler...

1456
01:27:02,175 --> 01:27:03,176
guilty as charged.

1457
01:27:03,801 --> 01:27:06,179
On the count of attempted murder
in the first degree

1458
01:27:06,262 --> 01:27:07,305
<i>of Kathy Kleiner...</i>

1459
01:27:07,847 --> 01:27:09,098
<i>guilty as charged.</i>

1460
01:27:09,557 --> 01:27:13,228
<i>On the count of attempted murder
in the first degree of Cheryl Thomas...</i>

1461
01:27:13,895 --> 01:27:15,146
<i>guilty as charged.</i>

1462
01:27:15,480 --> 01:27:16,564
<i>So say we all.</i>

1463
01:27:20,818 --> 01:27:23,196
<i> I consider the death penalty</i>

1464
01:27:23,321 --> 01:27:24,739
<i>to be one of the most</i>

1465
01:27:25,031 --> 01:27:25,907
<i>primitive,</i>

1466
01:27:26,074 --> 01:27:27,575
barbaric things

1467
01:27:28,701 --> 01:27:31,746
one human can impose on another.

1468
01:27:34,082 --> 01:27:36,626
My Christian upbringing tells me that

1469
01:27:36,709 --> 01:27:38,461
to take another's life

1470
01:27:39,420 --> 01:27:42,215
under any circumstance is wrong.

1471
01:27:44,092 --> 01:27:47,637
And I don't believe that the State of
Florida is above the laws of God.

1472
01:27:48,721 --> 01:27:49,847
Thank you, ma'am.

1473
01:27:51,557 --> 01:27:52,475
<i>Bless you.</i>

1474
01:27:54,936 --> 01:27:57,146
<i>While I certainly agree it is...</i>

1475
01:27:58,523 --> 01:28:00,441
<i>always a tragedy</i>

1476
01:28:00,817 --> 01:28:04,862
<i>when any life is taken
against one's will...</i>

1477
01:28:09,117 --> 01:28:11,703
it is this court's reasoned judgement

1478
01:28:11,786 --> 01:28:16,291
you be adjudicated guilty
of murder in the first degree...

1479
01:28:17,250 --> 01:28:20,003
that the killings were indeed

1480
01:28:20,295 --> 01:28:24,090
atrocious and cruel in that they were

1481
01:28:24,257 --> 01:28:26,092
extremely wicked,

1482
01:28:27,010 --> 01:28:28,678
shockingly evil,

1483
01:28:29,887 --> 01:28:30,847
vile...

1484
01:28:31,306 --> 01:28:34,350
and with utter indifference to human life

1485
01:28:34,434 --> 01:28:38,771
and that you shall be put to death
by current of electricity

1486
01:28:38,896 --> 01:28:40,857
that shall pass through your body

1487
01:28:40,940 --> 01:28:42,275
until you are dead.

1488
01:28:43,318 --> 01:28:46,029
I understand you have
a statement you'd like to make,

1489
01:28:46,112 --> 01:28:47,697
